What’s the difference between PhotonVision and WPILibPi? Our team is new to vision processing and needs clarification about implementing either.

We followed the tutorial on the WPILibPi page and can view the camera on it, but we don’t know where to go from here or if we should switch to PhotonVision.

Any help is appreciated; we’re really confused.

Hi there, WPILibPi is only a container for your own OpenCV code. It’s not a fully-fledged solution like PhotonVision or Limelight are. If you’re looking for something you can plug in and run, those two are what you want.

We have used WpiLibPi the last 3 seasons, it works well, but you will have to make your own vision pipelines with Python or Java to get vision working. GRIP helps a lot if you want to look at targets (either green light or colored targets).

We are actually switching to PhotonVision this season, you install it, then it will do pipeline processing like AprilTag finding, vision targets, or find color detection built it. You do a little bit of tuning in the GUI, and you have vision data. It will export the data using NetworkTables.

If you are just starting out, I would use PhotonVision, it’s pretty easy to configure and use. If you need more advanced vision processing, then WpiLibPi gives a nice container to run your custom scripts.
